@Styromaniac: I don't think integrating influx with ZeroNet is worth bothering Nofish about. IIRC he's working on deduplication atm, which is a far more important feature. It's also not something I want to force everyone to use as it requires running additional software next to ZeroNet (i.e. InfluxDB).

I don't have a Github account anymore, so I can't make an issue about it, feel free to bring it to his attention though if you wish.

@Draugrdeathlord: Technically it should, zerunet is being written in Rust and I'm avoiding platform-specific dependencies. Features like Tor, I2P, Influx, IPFS, etc. will be optional, but are all cross-platform as well AFAIK. That said my testing rigs are all GNU/Linux.

@Aassddff ‚ú† Œ£ üáßüá∑ üëë: The security is based on ECIES/AES, same as ZeroMail, except it's Customer<->Vendor only. Due to ZeroNet limitations there's some metadata that will always remain public: certificate, timestamp of last sign, and size of data.json.
- data.json is padded to lessen this metadata.
- it is up to customers to follow proper opsec when it comes to their certificate
